oes, gods as founders of their own cult, tombs of gods, euergetism, rationalistic interpretation of myths, the explanations of the origin of religion by the sophists, the ruler cult). The description of the Panchaian society is intended to suggest an archaic and closed culture, in which the stele recording res gestae of the deified kings might have been preserved. The translation of Ennius’ Euhemerus sive Sacra historia (ca. 200 - ca. 194) is a free prose rendering, which Lactantius knew only indirectly. The book is concluded by a short history of Euhemerism in the pagan, Christian and Jewish literature.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aEuhemerismus. 4aGriechische Religion. 4aHerrscherkult. 4aUtopische Insel. 4aUtopischer Roman. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEuhemerism.  aGreek religion.  aruler cult.  autopia.  autopian novel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE CLASSICAL STUDIES 2013z9783110317107oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUMSWISS. 2013z9783110317091oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311027888040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311029488040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110294880423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110294880/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlis